default3.1 To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers taken into account? default3.2 The following comments relate to bus services and community transport.
default3.3 Cu
defaultrrent bus users are mainly elderly, young people who haven’t passed their driving test yet or can’t afford to drive, young mothers, people with a variety of disabilities – often with mental health problems, poorer people; in short, the disadvantaged. Peopl
defaulte like myself, who choose bus use for conscientious reasons, are rare. 
default3.4 Any survey done specifically to find out how rural bus transport can be improved would gain the views of these disadvantaged people. As stated in the previous paragraph, these surv
defaulteys are not carried out. 
default3.5 Voluntary groups such as Ceredigion Association of Voluntary Organisations (CAVO) do have wide knowledge and try to address specific problems such as organising hospital transport. In Ceredigion CAVO has also introduced a whee
defaultlchair-adapted vehicle to their service, which can be hired. 
default&#xa0;
default4.1 What are the challenges with providing better bus and train services in rural areas?default4.2 The challenges are really the same as elsewhere. The only difference is that there are bigger gaps
default between the stops. 
default4.3 Where train lines are still operating, trains are very overcrowded, especially at certain times of the year. Extra services can be made part of a new franchise. 
default4.4.1 Where train lines have been closed, buses must fulfil their rol
defaulte. The Welsh Government has a strategy for putting on long distance fast services in preference to renewing rail tracks. This strategy has been only partly successful. 
default4.4.2 One of the failures is due to the cost of the tender. Operators have found themse
defaultlves unable to meet the demands set. 
default4.4.3 Another failure has been due to the supplanting of existing services that are hail and ride – they stop in small villages, at farm gates, etc – with a service that shoots past the very people who patronised the p
defaultrevious service. As a result many rural dwellers have lost their service.
default4.4.4 So the challenge is in how to increase patronage whilst not losing the current crop of users. 
