default5.1 How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengdefaulters?default5.2 Community Transport is variable. It is very good in some places and poor in others. It is good at helping a certain type of customer but not good at operating in a certain geographical area. 
default5.3 Users see themselves as charity cases. Drivers are usually volunteers. This does not make users feel comfortable. 
default5.4 Community Transport is often a sticking plaster and is not the answer. 
